src=3D"UI_EmpireNavigationTool_files/image005.png" align=3Dleft hspace=3D12=
 v:shapes=3D"Picture_x0020_3"><![endif]><span
lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>If you are zoomed out to Gal=
axy- or
Sector-level, as your mouse hovers over each item its location is
&#8216;pinged&#8217; in the galaxy with an expanding yellow circle.<o:p></o=
:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>C=
lick an
item in a list to select it in the Selection Panel below. You can then use =
the
Action buttons under the Selection Panel to access common tasks for the
selected item.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>D=
ouble-clicking
an item in a list will move the main view to that item.<o:p></o:p></span></=
p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>S=
ome of the
lists allow you to multi-select ships (shift-click) and perform actions on =
them
as a group. Thus from the &#8220;Military Ships&#8221; list you can shift-c=
lick
items to select a group of military ships, and then form them into a fleet =
by
clicking the &#8220;Create New Fleet&#8221; Action button below the Selecti=
on
Panel.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h3><span lang=3DEN-GB>Enemy Targets List</span></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id=3D"Picture_x0020_2" o:s=
pid=3D"_x0000_s1026"
 type=3D"#_x0000_t75" style=3D'position:absolute;margin-left:66.75pt;margin=
-top:0;
 width:117.95pt;height:185.35pt;z-index:251658240;visibility:visible;
 mso-wrap-style:square;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent:0;
 mso-wrap-distance-left:9pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:0;mso-wrap-distance-right=
:9pt;
 mso-wrap-distance-bottom:0;mso-position-horizontal:right;
 mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;mso-position-vertical:absolute;
 mso-position-vertical-relative:text;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent=
:0;
 mso-width-relative:page;mso-height-relative:page'>
 <v:imagedata src=3D"UI_EmpireNavigationTool_files/image007.png" o:title=3D=
""/>
 <w:wrap type=3D"square"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=3D157 height=3D247
src=3D"UI_EmpireNavigationTool_files/image006.png" align=3Dright hspace=3D1=
2 v:shapes=3D"Picture_x0020_2"><![endif]><span
lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>One notable list in the Empi=
re
Navigation Tool is the Enemy Targets List. This list shows you all known en=
emy
targets. Clicking on a target will assign your nearest available fleet to
attack it. Right-clicking on a target that has a fleet assigned will cancel=
 the
attack.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>I=
f you have
a fleet selected when you click a target, then the selected fleet will be
assigned to attack the target. Thus you can cycle through your fleets using=
 the
F key and assign attack targets by clicking in the Enemy Targets list.<o:p>=
</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB'>C=
licking on
a target that already has a fleet attacking it will instead select the assi=
gned
fleet. If you want to reassign the fleet you can then right-click the curre=
nt
target to cancel the attack and then click on the new target to attack it w=
ith
the selected fleet.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

</body>

</html>

